Uses of Class
com.i2group.apollo.auditservice.transport.AuditResults

  • Packages that use AuditResults 
    Package Description
    com.i2group.apollo.auditservice
    The i2 Analyze audit service provides clients with the ability to retrieve audit information about changes to items in the Analysis Repository.

    Calls to methods in this service must include a SOAP header containing an element named <ApolloMetadata> with an attribute named TimeZone. The value of the TimeZone attribute indicates the time zone that the client requires dates and times to be sent and displayed in.

    • Uses of AuditResults in com.i2group.apollo.auditservice

      Methods in com.i2group.apollo.auditservice that return AuditResults 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      AuditResults IAuditService.retrieveAuditEntries(Calendar fromDate, Calendar toDate)
      Retrieves AuditResults containing AuditEntrys with timestamps between the specified dates.
